A vintage 1930s Depression-era style illustration showing a row of identical American suburban houses slowly sinking into quicksand, their foundations crumbling and tilting at various angles. In the foreground, oversized playing cards featuring kings and queens are scattered and half-submerged in the sandy ground, their faces cracked and faded. The color palette uses muted sepia tones, dusty yellows, and faded reds. The sky is an ominous amber with dark storm clouds gathering on the horizon. The scene has the weathered texture of old newspaper lithographs with visible grain and slight color misregistration typical of vintage printing techniques.
